An order of the Lords Spiritual and Temporal assembled at Westminster, for the not observing the sixth day of February. Dies Sabbati Febr. 2d. 1788/9 [sic]. England and Wales. Parliament. House of Lords.
1 sheet (2 p.).
Printed by Edward Jones, for James Patridge and Samuel Heyrick., London, : 1688/9 [i.e. 1689]
Caption title. Printed with: A letter to a friend advising in this extraordinary juncture, how to free the nation from slavery for ever. London, : Printed for Abel Roper, at the Bell in Fleet-street, 1689. This is another setting of Wing L1638 which maybe found at reel 1152:21. Reproduction of original in the Sutro Library.
